---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Work With Me | SS Developers" description="The kinds of websites, apps, internal tools, trading systems, and fintech software I take on, and where I am not the right fit.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero-layout">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="page-intro">Work with me</div>
        <h1 class="page-title">The fit is strongest when the work needs clear ownership.</h1>
        <p class="page-copy">
          I do my best work when one careful builder can carry the work from framing through launch. That can be a website, a web app, internal software, or a specialist system where the logic underneath needs real care.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="availability-card">
        <small>Best fit</small>
        <strong>Focused builds, not committee projects</strong>
        <p>I prefer projects where the technical decisions have real consequences for trust, money, operations, or the day-to-day usability of the product.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container content-split">
      <div class="stack-lg">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div class="page-intro">Where I add the most value</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">The work is broad, but the ownership is specific.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="prose-block">
          <p>
            I do my best work on systems that need careful architecture: trading infrastructure, fintech products, cross-platform builds, and business software where getting the logic wrong costs real money, time, or trust. I am also happy to build websites and apps for clients who want one person carrying the whole thing, not a committee.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm probably not the right fit if you need a large retained team, or if the project is mostly content management with no custom engineering.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="manifest">
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>Websites and web apps</strong>
          <p>Marketing sites, product surfaces, and customer-facing builds that still need solid technical foundations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>Business software and automation</strong>
          <p>Operational tooling that reduces manual drift and gives the team a clearer picture of what is happening.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>Internal tools and dashboards</strong>
          <p>Interfaces for teams who need the system state to be legible, auditable, and easy to act on.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="manifest-row">
          <strong>Trading and fintech systems</strong>
          <p>Specialist work where authority, reconciliation, payouts, or trust-heavy flows deserve extra care.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/contact" class="button-primary">Start the conversation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
